{"recipe": [{"text": "\nThe Simply Recipe team puts out hundreds of recipes a year\u2014and while we love each and every one for different reasons, there are some that get more playing time in our own kitchens. These are the recipes that make busy weeknights less hectic, our lunches more exciting, and our dessert spreads at Thanksgiving that much more enjoyable. Out of all the recipes we published in 2021, here are the 10 that the Simply Recipes editors are happy to call their favorites.\n", "type": "text"}, {"image_link": null, "type": "image"}, {"text": "\nLooking for an easy weeknight recipe for 2022? This sheet pan dinner is a clear winner. \u201cI love this recipe because it\u2019s an all-in-one dinner with minor cleanup, and that\u2019s what I need for busy weeknights,\u201d explains Senior Editor Summer Miller. \u201cI can mix up the vegetables based on what I have and everyone loves it.\u201d\n", "type": "text"}, {"image_link": "https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/EMY0F3yOhCJPRoXPGAgrQtBtbSA=/3044x2029/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Simply-Recipes-Spinach-Banchan-LEAD-2-6d22429517024d20a899e5a0f5eed764.jpg", "type": "image"}, {"text": "\nSigeumchi Namul is a flavorful spinach side dish you\u2019ll want to eat on repeat. \u201cThis is your entry ticket into the world of Korean banchan,\u201d says Editor Myo Quinn. \u201cDon\u2019t be surprised if you find yourself drizzling sesame oil on everything.\u201d\n", "type": "text"}, {"image_link": "https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/T3Kp-PCcsmMCu4tjRtb7SY5K_UQ=/3142x2095/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Simply-Recipes-Green-Tahini-Sauce-LEAD-4-bd02353e20d14d729a51e8f0e62d0875.jpg", "type": "image"}, {"text": "\nLiven up your grain bowls with this quick green tahini sauce! \u201cThis has become a go-to,\u201d says Senior Editor Sara Bir. \u201cIt's quick to whip up in the summer when I have assorted fresh herbs; I love that it works with just one herb, like parsley, or a mix of others like dill and cilantro.\u201d\n", "type": "text"}, {"image_link": "https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/Tp7BpflvHXOCDa_TV5XaWMwwyIU=/6240x4160/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Simply-Recipes-Cherry-Cake-LEAD-2-cc1adab6eaea4c309ce993513fe5095f.jpg", "type": "image"}, {"text": "\nA cake that works for breakfast and dessert? Sign me up! \u201cI basically buy cherries every chance I get and to find a recipe that incorporates them into a buttery snacking cake is a dream come true,\u201d says Editor Milagros Cruz.\n", "type": "text"}, {"image_link": "https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/VkkseL63r_uSJ6x1knavkbxS-gE=/2000x1333/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/__opt__aboutcom__coeus__resources__content_migration__simply_recipes__uploads__2019__09__IP-Mushroom-Risotto-LEAD-7-9845e7cc033f4ceaa299834ab0855bd0.jpg", "type": "image"}, {"text": "\nWe talk about \u201cmagic-making\u201d recipes a lot at Simply Recipes\u2014the meals that can feed a family in no time, but also feel special. This is one of those dishes. \u201cThis recipe takes care of two constants in my kitchen: the mushrooms in my fridge that are starting to turn and the need for a quick dinner that feels luxurious,\u201d says Commerce Editor Siobhan Wallace.\n", "type": "text"}, {"image_link": "https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/J7rElTG0_sMsj3OcUoclJmzajVA=/2000x1333/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/__opt__aboutcom__coeus__resources__content_migration__simply_recipes__uploads__2020__12__Quick-Easy-Kimchi-LEAD-1-bd14c37616db435d9d999d5d38035e5b.jpg", "type": "image"}, {"text": "\n\u201cI love fermentation projects\u2014beer, sourdough, sauerkraut\u2014but for some reason hadn't yet tried my hand at kimchi,\u201d says Editor in Chief Emma Christensen. \u201cThis recipe changed that fast! I love this kimchi with rice bowls or turned into Kimchi Jjigae.\u201d Compared to traditional kimchi recipes, this recipe only takes a couple hours to prepare in order to eat (although it gets better as it ferments).\n", "type": "text"}, {"image_link": "https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/_0Qtwgu2N1KRUgT3Q6DBD0t2Fug=/5098x3399/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Simply-Recipes-Pumpkin-Basque-Cheesecake-LEAD-2-H-A-10f487fb5632420dbf3924c15e0fdc9a.jpg", "type": "image"}, {"text": "\nThis recipe from Karishma Pradhan was the star of my Thanksgiving dessert table this year. It\u2019s not fussy to make\u2014there\u2019s no water bath involved\u2014and the texture and flavor is just spot on. If you\u2019re not familiar with Basque-style cheesecake, it\u2019s essentially a cheesecake that \u201cself-crusts'' itself (so there\u2019s no graham cracker situation going on). I can\u2019t recommend it enough.\n", "type": "text"}, {"image_link": "https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/dXTmUqiyN-KJOxzl9MFafoza5Ug=/2832x1888/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Simply-Recipes-Cherry-Pop-Cocktail-LEAD-5_RECIRC-ad3b7f23c4d84bebabafa63370626d4d.jpg", "type": "image"}, {"text": "\n\u201cI love fizzy cocktails, especially when they include gin and Prosecco!\u201d Says Editorial Assistant Rachel Knecht. \u201cBlending the cherries means that I get the fresh cherry flavor in every sip.\u201d In addition to those three ingredients, all you need is some lemon juice and orgeat.\n", "type": "text"}, {"image_link": "https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/M_ox7NR_F6O9Q2I7fyb_CMssbQ0=/3900x2600/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Simply-Recipes-Yogurt-Cake-LEAD-12-58a82c5dfdb447d69f6b663528a2d381.jpg", "type": "image"}, {"text": "\n\u201cThis is an easy to make, tender cake that I can dress up or down for any occasion,\u201d says Summer. Top it with fresh fruit, whipped cream, or powdered sugar (or all of the above).\n", "type": "text"}, {"image_link": "https://www.simplyrecipes.com/thmb/3Q7cnlTuVZdNko42HqYBfrmqZtU=/4256x2832/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Simply-Recipes-Sheet-Pan-Sausage-Peppers-LEAD-3-b84160961a2f4d5397ba5a83e7e2adf0.jpg", "type": "image"}, {"text": "\n\u201cSheet pan meals are known for their easy clean up, but this one goes above and beyond by also taking less than 45 minutes and including less than 10 ingredients,\u201d says Rachel. \u201cItalian sausage has an abundance of flavor and is fuss-free, which makes this an easy family favorite.\u201d\n", "type": "text"}]}